  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. Since the ratio of <span class=\"italic\">y</span> to <span class=\"italic\">x</span> is constant for each ordered pair in the table, the first row can be used to determine that the ratio of <span class=\"italic\">y</span> to <span class=\"italic\">x</span> is 4 to 1. The proportion <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"4 over 1, equals k over 40 \"></span> can be used to solve for <span class=\"italic\">k</span>. Multiplying each side of the equation by 40 yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"160 equals k\"></span>.<span class=\"underline\"></span><p>Choice A is incorrect. This is the value of <span class=\"italic\">y</span> when the value of <span class=\"italic\">x</span> is 7, not 40. Choice B is incorrect and may result from subtracting 4 from 40 instead of multiplying 40 by 4. Choice C is incorrect and may result from incorrectly setting up the proportion.</p></p>\n",
